description: Recently sold: $288,500. A CLEAN CLASSIC all brick and stone mid-century rambler on a fabulous 1/3 acre corner lot; tucked away in one of Roseville's top neighborhoods. Spacious and welcoming layout with 3 bedrooms on the main level, full bath, shared kitchen/dining with gorgeous bow window overlooking the south facing backyard and patio, and an elegant living room offering an oversized east facing picture window, cove ceiling, flagstone entry, and stacked stone wood burning fireplace! Expansive lower level family room with adjacent hobby/rec room and 1/2 bath. Charming open front porch, tons of space to play in the front, side and backyard, mature trees, beautiful gardens and perennials, double wide concrete driveway for extra parking, and a storage shed. Freshly painted main floor and exterior front and south peaks. Ultra convenient location to parks, many schools, Rosedale mall, local eats, bus line and Hwy 36 to either downtown.

Recently sold: $111,648. Here's Main Level Living at it's Finest!  Address says #213 which most would figure 2nd Floor but is ground level (view photos). Gets better having a walkout patio to ease relaxation or go to your pool. There's an indoor heated pool/hot tub/sauna/basketball court/exercise room/party-amusement room w/ ping-pong and pool tables. Easy commute to anywhere and of course have a heated garage stall when winter comes again. Association fees covers heat/water/sewer/ High Speed Internet but not electricity. Be first and not last in seeing.

description:
Recently sold: $285,000. - New extra-deep 2 car garage (660 sq. ft.) in 2005 with storage in rafters and gutters
- Updated Kitchen in mid-1990's
- Hardwood floors refinished in 2000
- New roof and gutters in 2000
- Electrical service upgraded in 2001
- New refrigerator in 2002
- New furnace and AC in 2002
- New front walk and landscaping in 2006
- New asphalt driveway in 2007
- New exterior paint job in 2007
- New main floor bathroom in 2008
- New storm doors in 2008







Neighborhood Description



This neighborhood was built primarily in the 1950's and has a nice residential feel.  It is at a time of transition, where some original owners have retired in their homes and new families have moved in where original owners have moved on.  The neighborhood is well-kept and owners take pride in their properties and invest in upgrades; there are no junk houses in the vicinity.  The City of Roseville has an excellent street maintenance program so roads are all in great condition.  

The people that live here are salt of the earth, just really good people and great neighbors.  We know all our neighbors by first name, and down the street one family hosts an ice-cream social each August and this draws 50-75 people, almost a little block party.

There are neighborhood parks at each end of Merrill Street, and one of the parks connects to the excellent Roseville Parks and Trail system, which has miles of dedicated walking and biking paths.  The bandshell at Central Park is a 15 minute walk, which makes for fun summer outings to hear live music in the park.  The world class skating oval is only a few blocks away for recreational ice and inline skating.
